Explicitly include <tbb/version.h> so TBB_INTERFACE_VERSION_MAJOR is defined.

OpenUSD's workTBB backend relies on <tbb/blocked_range.h> to transitively
pull in the TBB version header (and thus define TBB_INTERFACE_VERSION_MAJOR)
before deciding between the legacy tbb::task API and the oneTBB task_group
API. This is no longer true with recent oneTBB releases (>= 2021/12.18, the
"tbb 2023" conda-forge migration), where <tbb/blocked_range.h> does not
define TBB_INTERFACE_VERSION_MAJOR. As a result the `#if
TBB_INTERFACE_VERSION_MAJOR >= 12` guard evaluates as false and the code
falls back to the removed legacy tbb::task / tbb::empty_task /
tbb::task_group_context API, failing to compile.

Including <tbb/version.h> explicitly guarantees the macro is defined for the
preprocessor checks. The header is available in all relevant TBB versions.

diff --git a/pxr/base/work/workTBB/dispatcher_impl.h b/pxr/base/work/workTBB/dispatcher_impl.h
--- a/pxr/base/work/workTBB/dispatcher_impl.h
+++ b/pxr/base/work/workTBB/dispatcher_impl.h
@@ -13,6 +13,7 @@
 // Blocked range is not used in this file, but this header happens to pull in
 // the TBB version header in a way that works in all TBB versions.
 #include <tbb/blocked_range.h>
+#include <tbb/version.h>
 #include <tbb/concurrent_vector.h>
 #if TBB_INTERFACE_VERSION_MAJOR >= 12
 #include <tbb/task_group.h>
diff --git a/pxr/base/work/workTBB/detachedTask_impl.h b/pxr/base/work/workTBB/detachedTask_impl.h
--- a/pxr/base/work/workTBB/detachedTask_impl.h
+++ b/pxr/base/work/workTBB/detachedTask_impl.h
@@ -10,5 +10,6 @@
 #include <tbb/blocked_range.h>
+#include <tbb/version.h>
 #include "pxr/base/work/workTBB/dispatcher_impl.h"
 #include "pxr/base/work/api.h"

 #if TBB_INTERFACE_VERSION_MAJOR >= 12
